<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-12-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-12-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="420" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d420">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Foster</persName> to Señor
                                    <persName type="to">Cayetano Romero</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-12-31"><hi rend="italic">December 31,
                                    1892</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Romero</hi>: I have received your note
                            of the 28th instant, and have hastened to bring to the notice of the
                            Secretary of War your suggestion relative to investigating the
                            contradictory statements made with reference to the Mexican soldiers
                            held at San Ignacio.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John W. Foster</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>